Product Specification: AI-Powered Job Application Autofill Chrome Extension
1. Product Overview

This Chrome extension helps job seekers apply to roles faster and with higher-quality answers.
It automatically parses any online job application form, extracts questions, and generates tailored, high-quality answers using the user‚Äôs CV or LinkedIn profile + their personal writing style.

The goal is to reduce friction, save time, and help candidates submit stronger applications at scale.

‚ú® 2. Target Users

Tech candidates (software engineers, PMs, designers).

Candidates applying to many roles in parallel.

People who struggle with writing answers about themselves.

Candidates with limited English or confidence in self-promotion.

üéØ 3. Core Value Proposition

Automatic form parsing ‚Üí No need to type repetitive details again and again.

AI-powered answers ‚Üí High-quality, personalized short/long answers.

Consistency with candidate identity ‚Üí Only uses the user's real CV data.

User voice ‚Üí User controls style, tone, level of confidence.

Time savings ‚Üí Apply to 5‚Äì10 jobs in the time usually needed for 1.

üß© 4. User Flow
4.1 Onboarding

Install extension ‚Üí click icon to begin.

Upload CV (PDF) or connect LinkedIn profile (via URL scraping + user permission).

User highlights sections: experience, projects, skills, summary.

Pick writing style:

Confident / humble

Concise / elaborate

Formal / casual

First person / third person

Set tone presets (e.g., ‚Äútechnical‚Äù, ‚Äúproduct-oriented‚Äù).

4.2 Using the Extension on an Application Page

User opens a job application page.

Extension scans the DOM and:

Detects text inputs

Detects textareas

Identifies questions (placeholder text, labels, aria labels)

Extension lists all questions in a side panel.

4.3 AI Answer Generation

For each question:

User clicks ‚ÄúGenerate Answer‚Äù

Model uses:

Parsed question

CV data + extracted achievements

Job description (optional ‚Äî detect automatically if in page)

User writing profile

Returns tailored answer.

User can edit manually.

User clicks ‚ÄúFill‚Äù ‚Üí autopopulates field.

4.4 Bulk Mode

User clicks ‚ÄúAuto-fill all answers‚Äù

Extension fills all fields (with review option).

4.5 Submission Tracking (later version)

Track which jobs the user applied to.

Save answers for reuse.

üì¶ 5. Core Features
5.1 Data Import

Upload CV (.pdf, .docx) ‚Üí parse into structured JSON.

Import LinkedIn ‚Üí scrape sections + convert into JSON.

User manually edits parsed data if needed.

5.2 Form Parser

DOM scanner detects:

<input type="text">

<textarea>

<select> (future)

Labels and surrounding context

Cleans and normalizes questions.

5.3 AI Answer Engine

For each question:

Classify question type:

Motivation (‚ÄúWhy do you want this role?‚Äù)

Experience (‚ÄúTell us about a project‚Ä¶‚Äù)

Skills (‚ÄúDescribe your knowledge of X‚Äù)

Behavioral (‚ÄúTell me about a challenge‚Ä¶‚Äù)

Generate answers using:

User skills + achievements

User-preferred tone

Job description context

5.4 Style Personalization

User can pick:

Voice tone (formal, friendly, confident, humble)

Length (short, medium, long)

Personality sliders (e.g., ‚Äúmore technical / more storytelling‚Äù)

‚öôÔ∏è Technical Specification
1. Architecture Overview
Chrome Extension
   |
   | (DOM parsing, UI)
   v
Local Processing Layer
   - CV parser (in-browser or backend)
   - Form scanner
   |
   | (API calls)
   v
Backend API (FastAPI or Node)
   |
   | (CV storage + embeddings)
   v
Vector DB (e.g., Pinecone, Qdrant, Supabase Vector)
   |
   | (Prompting engine)
   v
LLM (OpenAI API)

2. Chrome Extension Components
2.1 Content Script

Injected into every tab.

Responsibilities:

DOM scanning for fields

Extracting labels/questions

Watching for dynamically loaded forms (MutationObserver)

Providing mapping of field ‚Üí question

2.2 Popup & Side Panel

React UI (using chrome-extension-boilerplate)

Shows list of questions

Calls backend to generate answers

Auto-fills inputs via content script

2.3 Background Worker

Manages:

Auth session

Communication between popup ‚Üî content script

Caching answers

3. Backend Requirements
3.1 API Endpoints (FastAPI)
Endpoint	Method	Description
/upload_cv	POST	Upload + parse CV into structured data
/linkedin_scrape	POST	Scrape LinkedIn given HTML or public URL
/generate_answer	POST	Generate answer for a specific question
/save_style	POST	Save user style preferences
/health	GET	Liveness
3.2 CV Parser

Options:

Use OpenAI 5.1 structured extraction

Extract text locally + use regex heuristics

Use a Python NLP pipeline (Spacy + LLM refinement)

Output format:

{
  "name": "Adi Blum",
  "summary": "...",
  "experience": [
    {"company": "...", "role": "...", "achievements": ["...", "..."] },
  ],
  "skills": ["python", "aws", "system design"],
  "projects": [...]
}

3.3 Vector Search (optional but recommended)

Store each sentence from CV as an embedding.

During answer generation:

Retrieve relevant lines from CV

Provide evidence grounding

This enforces answers only based on the user‚Äôs real CV.

4. AI Prompting Logic
Prompt Template

Inputs:

Extracted question

User CV chunks (from vector retrieval)

Job description (optional)

User tone/style profile

Output Rules:

Must only use facts in CV.

Write in similar voice to user's settings.

Include specific achievements when relevant.

Stay concise unless user requested long style.

5. Tech Stack
Frontend (Extension)

TypeScript

React

Chrome Extension Manifest V3

Tailwind for styling

Vite build system

Backend

FastAPI (Python) or Node Express

PostgreSQL or Supabase (user settings)

Qdrant or Supabase Vector for embeddings

OpenAI API

6. Security & Privacy

CV stored encrypted in DB (or client-side only if local mode)

Everything is user-initiated (no hidden scraping)

Extension permissions:

activeTab

scripting

storage

No sensitive data sent except to your backend + OpenAI

